                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/3616: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Mayer</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-08T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >June 8, 1938—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. Reference my mail despatch No. 184, June 3.<note n="24" xml:id="d594fn24">Not
                        printed.</note> Pixley tells me that Leger has just informed him that he
                    intends to instruct De la Rue today by telegraph to begin negotiations with the
                    Foreign Bondholders Protective Council with regard to continuing the moratorium
                    on the amortization of the 1922 loan.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Mayer</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
